<activity xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="act-poly-infty-limit">

	<statement>
		<p>
			Completa la <xref ref="T-familiar-infty-limits">Tabla</xref> ingresando
			<q><m>\infty</m>,</q> <q><m>-\infty</m>,</q>
			<q><m>0</m>,</q> o <q>sin límite</q>
			para identificar cómo se comporta la función a medida que <m>x</m> aumenta o disminuye sin límite.
			En la medida de lo posible, trabaja para decidir el comportamiento <em>sin</em> usar una utilidad de graficación.
		</p>
		
		<table xml:id="T-familiar-infty-limits">
			<title>Algunas funciones familiares y sus límites cuando <m>x \to \infty</m> o <m>x \to -\infty</m>.</title>
			<tabular>
			    <row bottom="medium">
			      <cell><m>f(x)</m></cell>
			      <cell><m>\lim_{x \to \infty} f(x)</m></cell>
			      <cell><m>\lim_{x \to -\infty} f(x)</m></cell>
			    </row>
			    <row bottom="minor">
			      <cell><m>e^x</m></cell>
			      <cell><nbsp /></cell>
			      <cell><nbsp /></cell>
			    </row>
			    <row bottom="minor">
			      <cell><m>e^{-x}</m></cell>
			      <cell><nbsp /></cell>
			      <cell><nbsp /></cell>
			    </row>
			    <row bottom="minor">
			      <cell><m>\ln(x)</m></cell>
			      <cell><nbsp /></cell>
			      <cell><nbsp /></cell>
			    </row>
			    <row bottom="minor">
			      <cell><m>x</m></cell>
			      <cell><nbsp /></cell>
			      <cell><nbsp /></cell>
			    </row>
			    <row bottom="minor">
			      <cell><m>x^2</m></cell>
			      <cell><nbsp /></cell>
			      <cell><nbsp /></cell>
			    </row>
			    <row bottom="minor">
			      <cell><m>x^3</m></cell>
			      <cell><nbsp /></cell>
			      <cell><nbsp /></cell>
			    </row>
			    <row bottom="minor">
			      <cell><m>x^4</m></cell>
			      <cell><nbsp /></cell>
			      <cell><nbsp /></cell>
			    </row>
			    <row bottom="minor">
			      <cell><m>\frac{1}{x}</m></cell>
			      <cell><nbsp /></cell>
			      <cell><nbsp /></cell>
			    </row>
			    <row bottom="minor">
			      <cell><m>\frac{1}{x^2}</m></cell>
			      <cell><nbsp /></cell>
			      <cell><nbsp /></cell>
			    </row>
			    <row>
			      <cell><m>\sin(x)</m></cell>
			      <cell><nbsp /></cell>
			      <cell><nbsp /></cell>
			    </row>
			  </tabular>
		</table>
	</statement>
